<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <% include gtmHeader %>
    <% include style %>
<script type="text/javascript">
  function setClientId() {
	document.getElementById("clientId").value = Math.round(Math.random()*1000000000+1);
  } 
</script>
</head>
<body onload=setClientId()>
	<% include gtmBody %>
	<section>
    <p class="description">This node app takes in the images(jpg/png) that you feed it and passes it to <a href='https://ffmpeg.org'>ffmpeg</a>. It currently is a single pass, but I plan to use the <a href="http://blog.pkh.me/p/21-high-quality-gif-with-ffmpeg.html">multi-pass approach soon</a>.</p>
	</section>
	<section>
<form id="frm" method="post" action="/giffy" enctype="multipart/form-data">
  <input type="hidden" name="clientId" id="clientId" readonly>
  Select upto 50 (100kb&lt;) images: <input type="file" accept="image/png, image/jpeg" name="photos" multiple>
  <input type="submit">
</form>
<p>Try selecting more than one file when browsing for files.</p>
	</section>
<section>
<a href="/">home</a>
</section>
</body>
</html>
